  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Write custom agents. Not prompts."
    body="Most tools give you a prompt box. Codebolt gives you a 63-module SDK. Write agents in JavaScript with full access to filesystem, git, browser automation, terminal, LLM, vector database, memory systems, knowledge graphs, and more. Your agent connects as a child process, performs actions through the platform, and results appear in your workspace. This is agent programming, not prompt engineering."
    diagram={`codebolt.onMessage(async (msg) => {
  // Your agent logic
  const files = await codebolt.fs.readDir('/src');
  const code = await codebolt.fs.readFile('main.ts');
  const review = await codebolt.llm.chat(
    \`Review: \${code}\`
  );
  await codebolt.chat.sendMessage(review);
});
// 63+ modules available
`}
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Build applications as plugins. No separate agent needed."
    body="Plugins connect to the platform through three communication channels вҖ” WebSocket actions, multiplexed events, and HTTP REST. Unlike other SDKs, plugins run inside the agentic environment. They don't need to start their own agent instance. This means your CI/CD pipeline, code review system, or deployment automation runs natively inside the platform with full access to agentic capabilities."
