  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Governance, guardrails, and guardrails for guardrails."
    body="The policy engine evaluates rules and LLM classification for agent tool permissions. Scoped by agent role, agent ID, environment, provider, and execution phase. Decisions: allow, deny, or ask (require human approval). Per-agent and per-task LLM selection. Local model support including fine-tuned models. This is how you let agents run autonomously without losing control."
    reverse={true}
